div.span: We use git as a version control system. Git is the tool of choice as we already have some experience working with it as well as it being the de-facto standard in the software industry. Since we have to use GitHub as per requirement we are also facilitating that. Additionally we use the "branch and merge" strategy as a framework which we found our work on.

div.span: GitHub Actions is also used in this Project. We use the pipelines in order to do static analysis on our code, track dependencies (via. GitHubs own "dependabot" mechanism). Static analysis decides whether or not a branch can be merged ensuring code quality.

div.div: Built Docker images are uploaded to the GitHub Repository, which can be reached via ghcr.io. Each image carries a tag of the commit sha which it was generated from - allowing fine grained testing as well as version pinning for release candidates. As it is best practice we also update the "latest" tag with the latest image too.

div.span: The deployed Kubernetes cluster which has deployments for the backend, frontend as well as ingress and storage classes configures pulls the latest version from the Docker GitHub Repository and therefore always runs the latest version.
